cs.CV, cs.RO, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.CVPR

This paper is primarily focused on improving the accuracy of 3D object detection in autonomous driving using stereo images and sparse LiDAR sensors. Therefore, the most likely category is computer vision (cs.CV). The paper also deals with autonomous driving, which falls under robotics (cs.RO) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The proposed improvements in network architecture and loss function involve machine learning techniques, which could also place the paper in the category of machine learning (cs.LG). Finally, the paper presents results on the KITTI object detection benchmark, which is a popular computer vision conference (CVPR) dataset.
